Material Information Summary

Quarterly Report (June 2025)

  • Key Highlights:
  • Tabba Tabba Lithium Project:
    • PFS nearing completion; DFS testwork progressing (metallurgical, geotechnical, environmental).
    • 74.1Mt @ 1.0% Li₂O Mineral Resource Estimate (94% Indicated).
  • Exploration:
    • 2,380km² Pilbara land package; drilling at Bolt Cutter and Mt Adrah Gold Project (results pending).

  • Cash Balance: $55.1M (as of 30 June 2025).

  • Corporate Updates:

  • $5M on-market share buy-back announced (12-month period).
  • Jairo Bernal appointed CFO post-quarter.

Cash Flow (Appendix 5B)

  • Net Cash Outflows:
  • Operating: ($0.91M).
  • Investing: ($4.17M) – primarily exploration ($1.9M) and project studies ($2.2M).
  • Funding Runway: ~19.6 quarters based on current cash.

Forward Plans:

  • Complete PFS and advance DFS at Tabba Tabba.
  • Continue regional exploration programs.

No other material information identified.

• First SOF-SKN™ dose administered in the HERACLES clinical trial (first-in-human study).
  • Trial focus: Safety, tolerability, and dose-finding across four ascending dose cohorts.
  • Target market: Lupus (global market >US$3 billion), with potential expansion to psoriasis, atopic dermatitis, and other autoimmune diseases.
  • No financial or capital markets-related data (e.g., fundraising, cash balance, or material commercial agreements) disclosed.

Summary: Clinical milestone update only—no immediate trading or capital markets impact.

Material Information Summary (Duketon Mining Limited – June 2025 Quarterly Report)

Key Operational Highlights:

  • Killarney Gold Project (New Acquisition):
  • Option to acquire 100% of the project (cost: $50k upfront + 2M shares if exercised within 12 months).
  • Historic rock chip assays up to 485g/t Au; recent samples up to 51.5g/t Au.
  • Past small-scale mining yielded ~20kg Au from 4 tonnes.

  • New auger sampling identified a 250m gold anomaly (50ppb Au max).

  • Rosie Nickel Project (Resource Update):

  • JORC Resource: 2.77Mt @ 3.27% NiEq (56.3kt Ni, 11.8kt Cu, 229koz PGEs).

  • 72% in Indicated category; mineralization open in all directions.

  • C2 Nickel Project (Resource Update):

  • JORC Resource: 8.06Mt @ 0.57% Ni (46.3kt Ni, 25.7koz PGEs).
  • Combined Bulge Complex (Rosie + C2): 102.5kt Ni, 254.7koz PGEs.

Financial Position:

  • Cash & Liquids: A$11.7M (A$9.3M cash + A$2.4M shareholdings).
  • Quarterly exploration spend: A$231k.

Summary Focus: High-grade gold potential at Killarney and nickel resource updates dominate material news. Liquidity remains healthy (21 quarters of funding). No capital raising or trading halt noted.

Omitted: Routine tenement updates, regional exploration details, and non-material corporate disclosures.

Quarterly Report (Appendix 4C) Summary

Key Operational/Financial Highlights

  • Record production:
  • Q4 FY25: 7.01 PJe (77.1 TJe/d), +15% QoQ.
  • FY25: 26.64 PJe (73 TJe/d), +17% YoY (upper end of guidance).
  • Revenue:
  • Q4 FY25: $70.7M (+12% QoQ).
  • FY25: $267.7M (+22% YoY).
  • Average gas price: $10.11/GJ in Q4 (-1% QoQ); $9.91/GJ FY25 (+12% YoY).
  • OGPP performance: Produced at nameplate capacity (68 TJ/d) in June; potential capacity increase under evaluation.
  • East Coast Supply Project (ECSP):
  • Drilling (Elanora/Isabella) to commence Q2 FY26; FEED stage entered for subsea development.
  • Targeting FID H1 CY2026 and 90 TJ/d supply by 2028.
  • Net debt: $242.8M (-2% QoQ).
  • Cash balance: $62.4M (+11% QoQ).

Liquidity & Capital Structure

  • Drawn debt: $305.2M (unchanged QoQ).
  • FY25 capex: $60.7M (+154% YoY), primarily for ECSP.

Other Material Updates

  • Board changes: Chairman transition planned post-2025 AGM.
  • Asset exits: Agreements to divest Onshore Otway Basin interests (subject to approvals).

(Omitted: Routine operational details, director names, legal matters without material financial impact.)

Key Implications:

  • Cash Runway: Fully funded until profit distributions begin (H1 2026).
  • Project Focus: Supports exploration at Lucky Strike (1.27Mt @ 1.95g/t Au, 79,600oz) and broader Lefroy tenure.

Quarterly/Operational Summary:
- FY25 Hydro Generation: 3,410 GWh (17% ↓ YoY), 4th lowest since 1980 due to 12th percentile Waikato inflows.
- Total FY25 Generation: 7,906 GWh (11% ↓ YoY), with lower wind (-6%) and geothermal (-2%) output.
- FY26 Forward Prices: Auckland electricity futures at $179/MWh (FY26–27).
- Increased Mean Hydro Outlook: Uplift to 4,140 GWh/year (+62 GWh) from Digital River AI and Karāpiro rehab.
- Karāpiro Completion: Third unit replacement (Sep-25) adds 16.5MW capacity (+32 GWh/year at average inflows).
- Q4 Hydrology Recovery: Waikato inflows rebounded to 79th percentile, boosting storage for FY26.

Summary of ASX Announcement:

  • Infratil Limited (IFT) to be added to S&P/ASX 200 Index, effective 23 July 2025 (open of trading).
  • Replaces Spartan Resources Limited (SPR), which is being removed due to acquisition by Ramelius Resources Limited (RMS).

No other material information identified.

Here’s the material information extracted from the Meridian Energy June 2025 monthly operating report:

Key Highlights

Hydro Storage & Energy Metrics
- National hydro storage increased to 104% of historical average (up from 94%).
- South Island storage: 95% of average; North Island storage: 150% of average.
- June 2025 inflows: 111% of historical average.
- Waitaki catchment storage: 87% of average (37% higher YoY).

Electricity Demand & Pricing
- National demand: +1.4% YoY (June 2025 vs. June 2024).
- Retail sales volumes: +7.9% YoY; residential +12.7%, large business +15.2%.
- NZAS smelter load: 530MW (down YoY).
- Generation price received: -54.2% YoY in June 2025; -18.6% lower average price for Q4 YoY.

Operational & Financial
- Q4 2025 generation: 8.8% lower YoY.
- Capital expenditure: -16.5% YoY for Q4.
- Demand response termination agreement with NZAS to conclude by 11 August 2025.

Market Data
- Electricity futures prices declined across all winter quarters in Q4.
- NIWA winter 2025 outlook: above-average temperatures, normal/high rainfall.

Liquidity/Capital Structure Impact
No material changes to capital structure or funding disclosed.
